## A1 Relay Orchestrator Architecture
**Status:** draft
**Tags:** stack:backend, module:relay
**Depends on:** G2

# Relay Orchestrator Architecture

## Status: implemented ✅
**Last Verified**: 2025-01-15

## Overview

The Relay Orchestrator is a deterministic state machine in Rust that executes multi-agent flow specifications without LLM coordination overhead. It provides zero-token routing, predictable execution, and compile-time safety.

## Implementation Status

- ✅ **Implemented**: D2 (PipelineEngine & Flow Execution) is complete
- ✅ Core functionality: FlowSpec parsing, step execution, handoff routing, checkpoint management
- ✅ Gate enforcement: Human and auto-gates working
- ✅ Loop handling: Tester→Coder retry loops operational
- ✅ SSE events: Real-time progress updates implemented

## Key Components

- `PipelineEngine`: Main orchestrator state machine
- `FlowSpec`: Declarative flow definitions (standard, post_discovery, fast_track, bug_fix)
- `StepResult`: Step execution outcomes (Handoff, GateTriggered, LoopBack, Complete, Error)
- `PipelineStatus`: Runtime states (Idle, Running, WaitingForHuman, Completed, Failed, Paused)

## Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| Deterministic state machine vs LLM orchestrator | Zero token overhead, predictable routing |
| Rust implementation | Compile-time safety, performance |
| Checkpoint after every handoff | Crash recovery, resume capability |
| SSE events for progress | Real-time UI updates without polling |

## Dependencies

- D2: PipelineEngine & Flow Execution (implemented)
- D1: AgentInstance & Soul Rendering (implemented)
- D4: Checkpoint Serialization (implemented)

