## A2 Agent Instance Lifecycle
**Status:** draft
**Tags:** stack:backend, module:agent-config
**Depends on:** G1, G2

# Agent Instance Lifecycle

## Status: implemented ✅
**Last Verified**: 2025-01-15

## Overview

Agent instances are ephemeral spawned agents that exist only for the duration of a single pipeline step. They are created from Profession definitions, resolve their ModelConfig at spawn time, and execute ReAct loops with tool access control.

## Implementation Status

- ✅ **Implemented**: D1 (AgentInstance & Soul Rendering) is complete
- ✅ Agent spawning: `AgentInstance::spawn()` working
- ✅ Soul loading: Markdown souls loaded from `.autoforge/souls/`
- ✅ Model resolution: Fallback chains, tier-based selection
- ✅ Tool filtering: Profession-based `allowed_tools` enforcement
- ✅ Turn execution: ReAct loop with tool calls

## Key Components

- `AgentInstance`: Spawned agent with profession, soul, model, context
- `SoulConfig`: Markdown character definition
- `ModelConfig`: Provider, model, temperature, max_tokens, fallback_chain
- `AgentContext`: Budget tracking, files touched, turns taken

## Lifecycle

```
Unresolved → Resolved (Soul loaded)
Resolved → Ready (Model config validated)
Ready → Thinking (Turn started)
Thinking → ToolCall → Thinking (ReAct loop)
Thinking → Complete (LLM finishes)
Complete → Destroyed (Step done)
```

## Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| Ephemeral instances (step-scoped) | No state leakage between steps |
| Soul as markdown files | Easy editing, version control |
| Model resolution at spawn time | Allows per-agent provider selection |
| Tool allowlist per profession | Security, focused agent behavior |

## Dependencies

- D1: AgentInstance & Soul Rendering (implemented)
- A2: Relay Orchestrator (implemented)
- A7: API Source & Multi-Provider (in_progress)

