## A7 API Source & Multi-Provider Architecture
**Status:** in_progress
**Priority:** P0
**Tags:** stack:both, module:api-sources
**Depends on:** G13

# API Source & Multi-Provider Architecture

## Implementation Status

⚠️ **PARTIALLY IMPLEMENTED** - Critical Gap 2 (P0 Priority)

✅ **Completed**:
- D40: Model Tier 5-Level Expansion (Min/Lite/Mid/Large/Max) - implemented
- Backend: ModelTier enum with 5 variants
- Frontend: TIER_DISPLAY, TIER_DESCRIPTIONS, TIER_ORDER constants
- Agent defaults updated with new tier assignments
- Migration from legacy 3-tier (Light/Mid/Heavy) to 5-tier

❌ **Not Started**:
- D19: API Source Configuration (draft)
- D20: Multi-Provider AI Dispatch (draft)
- ApiSource CRUD operations
- Auto-detection of providers on startup
- Multi-provider dispatch_chat() function
- Test Connection endpoint
- ApiSourcesView.vue UI

## Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Config Layer"
        CF[config.rs] -->|load| AS[ApiSource Store]
        CF -->|load| AC[AgentConfig Store]
    end
    subgraph "Provider Dispatch"
        DP[dispatch_chat] --> AP[Anthropic Provider]
        DP --> OP[OpenAI Provider]
        DP --> LP[Local/Ollama Provider]
    end
    subgraph "Pipeline"
        PE[PipelineEngine] -->|resolve| RC[RelayRegistry]
        RC -->|spawn from| AC
        AC -->|uses| AS
        AS -->|routes via| DP
    end

    PE -->|step| AG[AgentInstance]
    AG -->|chat via| DP
```

## Trade-offs

| Approach | Pros | Cons |
|---|---|---|
| Multi-provider dispatcher with ApiSource configs | Per-agent model selection, cost optimization, provider flexibility | More complex AI dispatch layer, multiple SSE format parsers |
| Single provider with model tiers only | Simpler implementation | Locked into one provider, no fallback across providers |
| Runtime model registry (no config UI) | No UI needed | Users cannot manage API keys or discover models |

**Decision**: Multi-provider dispatcher with ApiSource configs

- ✅ Each agent can use the optimal provider + model for its task
- ✅ First-startup auto-detection finds existing keys — zero config for most users
- ✅ Test Connection endpoint validates setup before running pipelines
- ⚠️ Three different SSE parsing paths (Anthropic, OpenAI, Local) must be maintained
- ✅ Mitigation: OpenAI and Local share the same `/v1/chat/completions` format; only Anthropic differs

## Remaining Work

### Phase 1: Backend Core (3-4 days)
1. Implement `ApiSource` CRUD in `backend/src/relay/config.rs`
2. Implement `dispatch_chat()` multi-provider router
3. Add provider auto-detection on startup
4. Implement Test Connection endpoint

### Phase 2: Frontend UI (2-3 days)
1. Build ApiSourcesView.vue with provider management
2. Update AgentConfig resolution to use ApiSource store
3. Add migration from existing keys
4. Create first-startup onboarding flow

### Phase 3: Integration (1 day)
1. Update all agents to use ApiSource-based model resolution
2. Test fallback chains across providers
3. Verify tier optimization reduces token costs

## Success Criteria

- [ ] Auto-detects Anthropic, OpenAI, Local providers on first startup
- [ ] Users can configure multiple sources via UI
- [ ] Agents use different providers per model tier
- [ ] Test Connection endpoint validates credentials
- [ ] Fallback chain works across providers on API failure
- [ ] Token cost reduction >40% with tier optimization

## Related

- D19: API Source Configuration (draft)
- D20: Multi-Provider AI Dispatch (draft)
- D40: Model Tier 5-Level Expansion (implemented)
- G13: API Source Configuration (proposed)

