## A12 Errand Dispatch Architecture
**Status:** draft
**Tags:** stack:both, module:errand
**Depends on:** G22, A9

# Errand Dispatch Architecture

## Status: implemented ✅
**Last Verified**: 2025-01-15

## Overview

The errand dispatch system enables any profession to offload lightweight research tasks to a side agent (Gofer) that runs in an isolated message context. Only the final summary returns to the caller, keeping the master's chat history clean.

## Implementation Status

- ✅ **Implemented**: D28 (Dispatch Tool & Gofer Profession) is complete
- ✅ Dispatch tool: `dispatch` tool available to all relay professions
- ✅ Gofer profession: Minimal soul, cheap model tier, 20-turn limit
- ✅ Isolated context: ErrandSessions with separate message history
- ✅ Result compression: Only final assistant message returned
- ✅ Audit trail: Full errand logs persisted and visible in UI

## Key Components

- `DispatchTool`: Tool definition with agent, task, context parameters
- `ErrandSession`: Isolated session with parent_session_id, messages, status
- `Gofer` profession: Phase Errand, 6 tools, 4k token budget
- `ForgeStreamEvent`: ErrandStart, ErrandTurnStart, ErrandText, ErrandToolCall, ErrandComplete

## Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| Isolated ErrandSession | Master's chat history stays clean |
| Cheapest model tier (Min) | 80% token cost savings vs master model |
| Max 20 turns | Prevent runaway errands |
| Nested thread UI | Full audit visibility without clutter |

## Errand Lifecycle

```
Spawn (dispatch tool call)
→ Run isolated ReAct loop
→ Complete or Truncated (max turns)
→ Return summary to master
→ Persist full log to errands/ subdirectory
```

## Dependencies

- D28: Dispatch Tool & Gofer Profession (implemented)
- G22: Errand Agent Dispatch (implemented)
- A9: Chat-Turn Agent Handoff (proposed - uses similar pattern)

