## A13 Automatic Relay Mode Architecture
**Status:** draft
**Tags:** stack:both, module:relay
**Depends on:** G23, A1, A9, A12

# Automatic Relay Mode Architecture

## Status: implemented ✅
**Last Verified**: 2025-01-15

## Overview

Automatic Relay Mode enables chat agents (Advisor, Architect, Assistant) to spawn autonomous background relay pipelines via the `spawn_relay` tool. A background driver advances runs through steps, handles gates, and emits SSE events for real-time monitoring.

## Implementation Status

- ✅ **Implemented**: D29 (Spawn Relay Tool & Background Driver) is complete
- ✅ SpawnRelayTool: Available to assistant, advisor, architect professions
- ✅ Background driver: `relay::driver::drive_run()` with tokio tasks
- ✅ Flow templates: standard, post_discovery, fast_track, bug_fix
- ✅ Gate handling: 2-second polling for WaitForHuman gates
- ✅ SSE events: RelaySpawned, RelayUpdate, RelayGateWaiting, RelayComplete
- ✅ Chat integration: Relay cards in chat stream, monitor link to RelayView

## Key Components

- `SpawnRelayTool`: Tool with flow_id, task, mode, context parameters
- `relay::driver::drive_run()`: Background execution loop
- `RunStore`: In-memory run state storage
- `ForgeStreamEvent`: Relay events for chat frontend
- Step message construction: Task + previous handoff + gate feedback

## Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| Tool-based spawning | LLM controls when to spawn, not system watcher |
| Background tokio tasks | Non-blocking, multiple concurrent runs |
| 2-second gate polling | Simple, no complex channels |
| Post-discovery flow | Skip intake/discover for chat-initiated runs |

## Flow Templates

- **standard**: intake → discover → goal_gate → architect → planner → coder → tester → reviewer → documenter
- **post_discovery**: architect → planner → coder → tester → reviewer → documenter (chat→relay bridge)
- **fast_track**: coder only (simple fixes)
- **bug_fix**: tester → coder → tester → reviewer (test-driven fixes)

## Dependencies

- D29: Spawn Relay Tool & Background Driver (implemented)
- G23: Automatic Relay Mode (implemented)
- D2: PipelineEngine & Flow Execution (implemented)

---

**Verified against D29 implementation on 2025-01-15**

## A14 Goals Hierarchy Architecture
**Status:** draft
**Tags:** stack:frontend, module:specs

# Goals Hierarchy Architecture

## Status: implemented ✅
**Last Verified**: 2025-01-15

## Overview

The Goals Hierarchy system enables one-level-deep parent-child relationships between goals (e.g., G9.1 is a child of G9). Subgoals are detected automatically via dotted ID notation, rendered in a tree view with collapsed-by-default branches, and filtered by typed tags.

## Implementation Status

- ✅ **Implemented**: D35-D37 (Goals Tree, DetailModal, Filtering) are complete
- ✅ Tree view: Recursive GoalNode component with expand/collapse
- ✅ ID parsing: Automatic subgoal detection (G9.1 → child of G9)
- ✅ Detail modal: Inline edit, RelationsPanel, status transitions
- ✅ Typed tags: `kind:value` format (stack:frontend, module:specs)
- ✅ Sidebar filtering: Stack and Module multi-select drawers

## Key Components

- **Backend**: 
  - `get_goals_tree()` API: Pre-built hierarchical structure
  - `validate_goal()` API: ID format, parent reference, depth checks
- **Frontend**:
  - `GoalsTable.vue`: Tree container with filtering
  - `GoalNode.vue`: Recursive node component (collapsed by default)
  - `GoalDetailModal.vue`: Detail view with inline edit mode
  - `TagBadge.vue`: Color-coded tag display
  - `useGoalsTree`: Singleton composable with expand state persistence

## Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| One-level depth only (G9.1 ok, G9.1.2 invalid) | Simplicity, prevents deep nesting |
| Dotted ID notation | No manual parent_id field needed |
| All branches collapsed by default | Performance-friendly for large trees |
| Modal for details (not inline expansion) | Clean tree UI, focused editing |
| Typed tags (kind:value) | Structured filtering, no separate category field |

## Data Model

```typescript
interface GoalNode {
  id: string
  title: string
  status: Status
  priority?: string
  tags: Tag[]
  children: GoalNode[]
  expanded: boolean  // Default: false
}
```

## Filtering Logic

- **Search**: ID, title, tag values (auto-expands matching branches)
- **Stack filter**: Match any `stack:*` tag
- **Module filter**: Match any `module:*` tag
- **AND logic**: Item must match stack AND module if both selected

## Dependencies

- D35: GoalsTable Tree View Component (implemented)
- D36: GoalDetailModal Component (implemented)
- D37: Spec Tag Display & Sidebar Filtering (implemented)
- G21: Hierarchical Goals View (implemented)

